{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/48256","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/48256/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/48256/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/48256/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/48256","id":1717796292,"node_id":"I_kwDNIULOZmN9xA","number":48256,"title":"`html_escape_once` decodes items flagged `html_safe`","user":{"login":"antemasqued","id":35539116,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1NTM5MTE2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/35539116?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued","html_url":"https://github.com/antemasqued","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/antemasqued/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2023-05-19T20:37:21Z","updated_at":"2023-05-22T16:03:10Z","closed_at":"2023-05-22T10:03:37Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"If we mark something `html_safe`, we typically expect it to be rendered as-is and left alone. \r\n\r\nIf we utilize `html_escape_once` then somehow the above purpose of `html_safe` is neglected and that item is decoded. \r\n\r\nThis doesn't appear to be an uncaught edge case, but rather something done explicitly as is shown below ([ref](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/4e1fe73028f4b01c8e5179989511b21925f70b20/activesupport/lib/active_support/core_ext/erb/util.rb#L65))\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n# File activesupport/lib/active_support/core_ext/string/output_safety.rb, line 44\r\n    def html_escape_once(s)\r\n      result = s.to_s.gsub(HTML_ESCAPE_ONCE_REGEXP, HTML_ESCAPE)\r\n      s.html_safe? ? result.html_safe : result\r\n    end\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis seems to be inconsistent behavior as `html_escape` itself explicitly skips the escaping. What's the purpose of this? We have an explicit line here for this, so surely there was some thought put into this ðŸ¤”.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rails/rails/blob/4e1fe73028f4b01c8e5179989511b21925f70b20/activesupport/lib/active_support/core_ext/erb/util.rb#LL67C1-L67C47","closed_by":{"login":"byroot","id":44640,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ0NjQw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/44640?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot","html_url":"https://github.com/byroot","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/byroot/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":fals